Class WDLibrary.RBT

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.safs.selenium.webdriver.lib.WDLibrary.RBT
  • Enclosing class:
    WDLibrary

    public static class WDLibrary.RBT
extends java.lang.Object
    This class represents a Robot, which can do work locally (thru local org.safs.robot.Robot) or remotely (thru a RMI agent).
    Author:
    Lei Wang

      • click

        public static void click(java.awt.Point location,
                         org.openqa.selenium.Keys specialKey,
                         int mouseButtonNumber,
                         int nclicks)
                  throws java.lang.Exception
        Use Robot to click locally or remotely (through RMI). Use the current WebDriver as a RemoteDriver to provide an RMI agent.
        Parameters:
        location - Point, The screen location to click at.
        specialKey - Keys, The selenium Keys value, representing the key (such as Ctrl, Alt) pressed during mouse click.
        mouseButtonNumber - int, Representing the mouse button to click, such as WDLibrary.MOUSE_BUTTON_LEFT.
        nclicks - int, How many times to click mouse.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception

      • inputKeys

        public static java.lang.Object inputKeys(java.lang.String keys)
                                  throws SeleniumPlusException
        Type keyboard input. The input goes to the current keyboard focus target. The String input can include all special characters and processing as documented in the CreateUnicodeMap class.
        The input happens locally if the current RemoteDriver is null or is local; otherwise if the current RemoteDriver is remote, then it happens remotely.
        Parameters:
        keys - String, the keys to enter.
        Returns:
        Object Currently we return a Boolean(true) object, but this may be subject to change.
        Throws:
        SeleniumPlusException - if the "bypass robot" is set to true.

      • inputChars

        public static java.lang.Object inputChars(java.lang.String chars)
                                   throws SeleniumPlusException
        Type keyboard input characters unmodified. No special key processing. The input goes to the current keyboard focus target. The String input will be treated simply as literal text and typed as-is.
        The input happens locally if the current RemoteDriver is null or is local; otherwise if the current RemoteDriver is remote, then it happens remotely.
        Parameters:
        chars - String, the characters to enter.
        Returns:
        Object Currently we return a Boolean(true) object, but this may be subject to change.
        Throws:
        SeleniumPlusException

      • mouseWheel

        public static boolean mouseWheel(int wheelAmt)
                          throws SeleniumPlusException
        Scroll the mouse wheel by Java Robot.
        The scroll happens locally if the current RemoteDriver is null or is local; otherwise if the current RemoteDriver is remote, then it happens remotely.
        Parameters:
        wheelAmt - int, the wheel amount to scroll.
        Returns:
        boolean true, if the scroll succeeds.
        Throws:
        SeleniumPlusException - if the "bypass robot" is set to true.
